French sugar beet plantings are off to agood start, thanks to generally favourable winter and springweather, the CGB beet planters' association said.    It said in a report that soil structure was likely to beexcellent for good preparation as a result of a cold,reasonably showery, winter.    By April 15, 27.8 pct of the area had been sown againstthree pct at the same year ago date.    It added the area sown was likely to be reduced this yearby 1.2 pct to 445,000 hectares. REUTER&#3;